post_text:
Dear Families
In an effort to increase safety and timeliness with parent pick up in the afternoons, we have updated our protocols for Afternoon Parent Pick Up:

• Students with a ride home from a high school sibling will be dismissed at 12:46pm
• Students walking or biking home will be dismissed at 12:52pm
• Students with last names starting with the letters N-Z will have Parent Pick Up in the Lower Parking Lot from 12:58- 1:05PM.
• Students with last names starting with the letters G-M will have Parent Pick Up in the Lower Parking Lot from 1:10-1:17PM.
• Students with last names starting with the letters H-F will have Parent Pick Up in the Lower Parking Lot from 1:15-1:25PM.

Thank you for your understanding!

*If you time slot does not work for you, please email me at: Kristen_levesque@maranacook.com

post_text:
Thank you for your questions regarding the revised school calendar, in particular, the first student week and Wednesday 9/9. The calendar is correct; there will be school for students on Wednesday, 9/9. We found it important to hold school that day since Monday is a holiday, and Tuesday is the first student day for select grades.
To clarify, the first student day for Grades K-2, 6, and 9 is Tuesday, 9/8. The first student day for Grades PreK, 3-5, 7, 8, and 10-12 is Wednesday, 9/9. Students enrolled in the CATC program will attend school at MCHS on 9/9 and 9/10; their first day at the CATC program will be Friday, 9/11.
Sincerely,
Jay Charette

post_text: Way to go Awesome Bear Society! Excellent progress being made for the MARANACOOK ATHLETIC & RECREATION EXPANSION PROJECT!
shared_text:
Awesome Bear Society
June 24 at 1:01 PM ·

PHASE 1 CONSTRUCTION SITE PREPARATION COMPLETED!!

The week of June 15th saw the completion of major steps towards construction of restrooms in the concession courtyard. With assistance from Maine Equipment Rental, Shaun Drinkwater and Cushing Construction, the site around the concession stand has had all stumps, shrubs, old benches and old concrete super pavers removed and disposed of off site. With final engineering/construction plans due in by the end of June, it is hoped that actual construction will begin later this summer! Huge thank you's go out to Maine Equipment Rental, Shaun Drinkwater and Cushing Construction for their donations of delivery/pickup, operation and clean up/disposal of the courtyard area!! It is community support like this that helps bring such projects to life - THANK YOU!!!!

For more information about MARANACOOK ATHLETIC & RECREATION EXPANSION PROJECT, please visit our website at www.awesomebearsociety.com

post_text:
Student Belongings Pick Up & Laptop/ School Materials Drop Off
Students will need to return any school books and their school-issued laptops and devices on this day.
Students will also have one more opportunity to be given any belongings that were left in school.
A lost and found will also be set up on this day,and photos of the items will be sent out in upcoming newsletters, to help families search and identify items which belong to them.
June 9, 7:30-11:30am: 7th grade and any 8th graders who did not come yesterday
June 10, 7:30-11:30am: 6th grade and anyone else who still needs to drop their MCMS laptops off
*This is a curbside drop off/ pick up only. Students and Parents are required to stay in their vehicles during this.
*Families with more than one child at the middle school are able to pick up on one day only. Please communicate with their children’s advisor as to what day you are coming.

post_text:
Virtual Humanities Night at MCHS!

This year, we needed to highlight student work differently. Our Fine Arts Department staff created this website MCHS Humanities Night 2020 https://sites.google.com/maranacook.com/mchshumanitiesnight2020/virtual-humanities-night-home to showcase the work of Maranacook music and visual art students from the 2019-2020 year! While it is unfortunate that we could not celebrate under normal circumstances, we are happy to share with the community the work that has been created throughout the year, from metalwork to sketches, and original student compositions to live performances. The V&PA department hopes that in these trying times, the community can benefit from the creative energies of its youth.

~Dan Gilbert, Tom Ferrero & Jeremy Smith

post_text:
End of the School Year Student Belongings Pick Up and Laptop/ School Materials Drop Off
MCMS will be holding their End of the Year Drop Off/ Pick Up Days on June 8, 9th and 10th.
Students will need to return any school books and their school-issued laptops and devices on this day.
Students will also have one more opportunity to be given any belongings that were left in school.
A lost and found will also be set up on this day,and photos of the items will be sent out in upcoming newsletters, to help families search and identify items which belong to them.
June 8, 7:30-11:30am: 8th grade (8th graders encouraged to come, if able)
June 9, 7:30-11:30am: 7th grade
June 10, 7:30-11:30am: 6th grade
*Families with more than one child at the middle school are able to pick up on one day only. Please communicate with your children’s advisor as to what day you are coming.
8th grade families are asked to come on June 8 as there will be some special recognition!

REGIONAL SCHOOL UNIT #38
REQUEST FOR PROPOSAL
ASPHALT PAVING SERVICES

Regional School Unit #38 is seeking requests for bids from qualified firms for asphalt paving services at the following location: RSU #38 Bus Garage, 73 North Road, Readfield Maine 04355. Installation must be completed by August 21, 2020.

A mandatory pre-bid walk through will be held on May 5, 2020, 10:00 a.m., at 73 North Road, Readfield Maine 04355, at which time additional information will be provided to potential bidders.

Bids must be submitted in writing, in a sealed envelope labeled “ASPHALT PAVING SERVICES BID”, and received no later than 11:00 a.m., Thursday, May 21, 2020 at RSU #38, 45 Millard Harrison Dr., Readfield, ME 04355. RSU #38 reserves the right to reject any and all bids.

Remote Learning Prep: Essential School Materials Pick Up Information

Starting Monday March 30, 2020, we will be starting Remote Learning. Students will have access to materials for learning on Google Classroom.
If your child is in need of hard copies, or has any needed materials, please contact your child's advisor by 5pm, Tuesday 3/24, to arrange the pickup or delivery

Things will be gathered and ready on Friday March 27th at the following times:
7:30-9am
4-5pm
Unfortunately, no students or parents will be allowed in the building; this will be a drive up service only.

Home delivery can also be arranged- this will occur on 3/27 during the hours of 9-2pm. (Please contact your child’s advisor to set this up)
Please call us or email us with any questions.

We would ask each school to treat this time similarly to how you would treat the hands-off time between seasons and during the two-week period in early August.
